  <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Buyer's guide</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">How to choose the right <span class="accent">SEO content autopilot tool.</span></h2>
      <p>If you're evaluating options beyond this list, here's the decision framework we'd apply ourselves.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Start with the pipeline question: do you want to supply keywords, or have the tool find them?</h4>
              <p>If you want to supply keywords: Byword, Journalist AI, Koala.sh, or SEOWriting.ai. If you want zero input beyond business description: theStacc or Autoblogging.ai.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Decide whether you want brand voice or volume</h4>
              <p>For local businesses that need content to sound like them: theStacc or Writesonic. For programmatic volume where template consistency is fine: Byword or SEOWriting.ai.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Check which CMS platforms are supported before signing up</h4>
              <p>Autoblogging.ai and Journalist AI are primarily WordPress. theStacc, Byword, and most others support multiple platforms. Verify your CMS is covered before committing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Don't conflate content generation tools with content autopilot tools</h4>
              <p>Jasper, ChatGPT, and Claude generate content. They are not autopilot tools. Autopilot means the content publishes on a schedule without you pressing a button. Most tools in this list are autopilot. Jasper and ChatGPT are not.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Verify what happens to content if you cancel</h4>
              <p>With theStacc: every article stays on your site forever. With most tools: your content is in your CMS and it stays there on cancellation. Confirm content portability with any tool before committing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

